    "name": "GARDENS CABIN",
    "detail": "The hotel was sparkling clean, beds were well made and the guests were separated far enough so they wouldn't disturb each other at night. The toilets on each floor were also very clean with everything you need including the hair straightener, body lotion etc.! Independent and clean shower rooms are available only in the basement level with the public bath. Though Sapporo and Japan is generally quite safe, two recommendations I have for the hotel would be: 1. At the public bath level, staff someone to ensure the safety of female residents, because this level is open to the public, it is a little scary to go down alone at night. 2. The curtains to seal off the cabin is really sound proof, but makes it a little stuffy inside as well, suggest to have independent heat controls and small fan in the cabin for better ventilation Nonetheless the hotel offers superb value for money, the staff was also very helpful, would recommend it to any solo travelers.",
