    "name": "KEIO PRELIA HOTEL SAPPORO",
    "detail": "This is my first time staying in this hotel. Hotel itself as Keio, this hotel is a very nice and clean hotel. It looks spacious, but the rooms are just average size in Japan. Hokkaido in general, the rooms are bigger than hotels in Tokyo. So as for us, it was not spacious but just average. This hotel is about 5 min walk from Sapporo Station. If you are using Jr passes, this hotel will be very convenient to travel to other places in Hokkaido. Also, this hotel is near Sapporo underground shopping center, so if it is too cold or hot, you can walk through the underground pass to avoid the weather. However, if you are looking to stay near Odori park, it is a bit of walk, or a station away. I would recommend hotels near Odori park. We would only stay again if the price is reasonable again.",
